an a range of orbital\neccentricities, periods, and spectral types for the red-giant companion. One\ncase even suggests a system composed of two red-giants. The discovery of\npulsating red giants in multiple systems provides exciting test beds for\nprecise astrophysical modeling, and follow-up spectroscopic observations of the\ncandidate systems are encouraged.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Mar 2013 21:57:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
